  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of the study is to assess the dying process in critically ill patients with
      decision to withdraw invasive mechanical ventilation in anticipation of death and to compare
      effects of extubation and those of terminal weaning of mechanical ventilation on relatives
      and care givers. The investigators primary hypothesis is that extubation is associated with
      less symptoms of post-traumatic stress disorders in relatives, as compared to terminal
      weaning.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
